# Commit Messages

Use Conventional Commits for non-merge commit subjects:

```text
<type>[optional scope]: <description>
```

Keep subjects concise and imperative. Use a body only when the reason is not obvious from the diff.

Use the standard Conventional Commit types when they fit, and allow `cleanup:` as a repo-local type for small behavior-preserving smell fixes.
